provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py, Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures.Future — __name__=='Future' (len=6), __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); Future.__init__ co_argcount==1; Future.result.__qualname__=='Future.result' (len=13), co_argcount==2, co_varnames.__len__()==2; Future.add_done_callback.__qualname__=='Future.add_done_callback' (len=24), co_argcount==2. concurrent.futures.Executor — __name__=='Executor' (len=8), __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); Executor.map.__qualname__=='Executor.map' (len=12), co_argcount==2, co_varnames.__len__()==8; Executor.shutdown.__qualname__=='Executor.shutdown' (len=17), co_argcount==2, co_varnames.__len__()==3. Also concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor — __name__=='BrokenExecutor' (len=14), __bases__[0].__name__=='RuntimeError'. Also concurrent.futures.__spec__.__class__.__name__=='ModuleSpec' (len=10); __spec__.name=='concurrent.futures' (len=18). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7+'.'=1+'_base'=5=24); same module as Executor and BrokenExecutor. Future.__init__ co_argcount==1 ('self' only; Future is initialized with no extra args). Future.result co_varnames==('self','timeout') (len=2); Future.add_done_callback co_varnames==('self','fn') (len=2). Executor.map co_varnames len==8 ('self','fn','timeout','chunksize','buffersize','iterables','args','result_iterator'). Executor.shutdown co_varnames==('self','wait','cancel_futures') (len=3). BrokenExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__=='RuntimeError' (BrokenExecutor inherits from RuntimeError, not Exception). concurrent.futures.__spec__.name=='concurrent.futures' (len=18). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

